# CYBERSECURITY GAME - CONTEXT (NOT INSTRUCTIONS)

## Project Type
Educational cybersecurity investigation game (Next.js 14 + TypeScript + Tailwind)

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- React 18 + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS only
- localStorage for state
- NO backend/database

## Code Standards

### TypeScript
- Use strict mode
- Define interfaces for all data
- Avoid `any` type

### React Patterns
```typescript
// Use this pattern for components:
export function ComponentName({ prop }: Props) {
  const { state, dispatch } = useGame();
  
  const handleAction = useCallback(() => {
    // validation
    // dispatch action
    // side effects
  }, [deps]);
  
  return {/* JSX */};
}
```

### Tailwind
- Mobile-first (base, then md:, lg:)
- Use design system colors
- Avoid arbitrary values

### State Management
```typescript
// GameContext pattern:
interface GameState {
  credits: number;
  unlockedClues: string[];
  viewedClues: string[];
  chatHistory: ChatMessage[];
  accusationsMade: Accusation[];
  recoveryActions: string[];
  glossaryLookups: string[];
  gamePhase: 'investigation' | 'recovery' | 'ended';
  currentTab: string;
  endingType: 'A' | 'B' | 'C' | 'D' | null;
}

type GameAction = 
  | { type: 'SPEND_CREDITS'; amount: number }
  | { type: 'UNLOCK_CLUE'; clueId: string }
  | { type: 'MAKE_ACCUSATION'; suspectId: string };
```

## File Structure
```
app/          # Next.js pages
components/   # React components
context/      # GameContext
data/         # Game content (clues, suspects, glossary)
lib/          # Utilities
types/        # TypeScript interfaces
```

## DO ✅
- Show credit cost on ALL buttons
- Confirm expensive actions (10+ credits)
- Make terms clickable with [?] icon
- Auto-save to localStorage
- Test on mobile (320px) and desktop
- Use semantic HTML + ARIA labels

## DON'T ❌
- Don't show locked content before unlock
- Don't use external APIs
- Don't allow accidental credit spending
- Don't use custom CSS (Tailwind only)
- Don't generate ALL code at once (wait for requests)

